  'RichText.FAQ' => 
  array (
    '_attrs' => 
    array (
      'group' => 'F.A.Q.',
      'type' => 'WYSIWYG',
    ),
    'message' => '
			
				<ol>
					<li><b>How can I install update for the component?</b><br/>
					At first, uninstall of the component. This will remove all the files related to the component, but all the data will remain in the database. After this, install the new version of the component. That\'s it, the component is ready.
					<br /><br />
					<li><b>How can I add the point of the menu leading to the list of quizzes?</b><br/>
					Use Joomla Menu Manager:<br />
					- Click "New" Button.<br />
					- Select "Component" from the "Components" section.<br />
					- Choose ARI Quiz Lite component.<br />
					- Click "Save" Button.
					<br /><br />
					<li><b>How can I recognize Quiz ID?</b><br/>
					You can see it at the page with the list of quizzes, otherwise while updating a test.
					<br /><br />
					<li><b>How can I add the point of the menu leading to a definite quiz?</b><br/>
					The link will look the following way: index.php?option=com_ariquizlite&quiz_id=&amp;lt;Quiz ID&amp;gt;
					<br /><br />
					<li><b>Can users look through the statistics of the quizzes they passed?</b><br/>
					Yes, it is available to the registered users by the link index.php?option=com_ariquizlite&task=quiz_stat. For your convenience you can add appropriate menu item with this link. 
				</ol>
			
		',
    'description' => 'F.A.Q. text',
  ),
  'RichText.Help' => 
  array (
    '_attrs' => 
    array (
      'group' => 'Help',
      'type' => 'WYSIWYG',
    ),
    'message' => '
			
				<ol>
					<li><b>Quiz Categories</b><br/>
					Categories for questions are used to divide the quizzes according to the themes.<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Category</b><br/>
						To add a category click "Add" button at the page with the list of categories. For updating click the name of the category in the list of categories. While adding/updating you can define the following properties:<br/>
						- Category name;<br/>
						- Category description;<br/>
						<li><b>Category List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of categories is shown and there is a possibility to delete the selected categories.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />

					<li><b>Question Categories</b><br/>
					Is used if you want to create a review quiz on different themes. In this case, you add question category for the themes you need and give the appropriate question categories to the question created.
					<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Question Category</b><br/>
						To add question category click "Add" button at the page with the list of question categories, to update it click the name of the question category in the list of categories. While adding / updating, you can define the following properties:<br/>
						- You can choose a quiz it refers to.(If you are adding a new question category);<br/>
						- Category name;<br/>
						- Define the quantity of questions selected from category question pool while passing a quiz. If meaning "0" or empty is defined, all questions from the given category will be selected;<br/>
						- Define the amount of time given to think of the answer to the question from the given category. When the given time runs out, you pass to the next question. At this case the previous question is not counted. If meaning "0" or empty is defined, then an unlimited amount of time will be given to think of the answer;<br/>
						- Category description;<br/>
						<li><b>Question Category List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of question category is shown. You have a possibility to delete the selected categories. While deleting you will be requested: to delete the questions connected with the category or to make them not refering to any question category.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Question Templates</b><br/>
					In this section you can add question templates for creating new questions on the basis of basic type of questions (See section 9.c). It is used for the more convenient creation of frequently repeating options, for example: "Yes/No", "True/False".<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Question Template</b><br/>
						To create a question template click "Add" button at the page with the list of question templates. For updating click the name question template in the template list. While adding / updating you can define the following properties:<br/>
						- Template name;<br/>
						- Type of question (See section 9.c);<br/>
						- Activate / Deactivate validating question parameters while saving the template;<br/>
						- Define the parameters for the type of question selected;<br/>
						<li><b>Question Template List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of question templates is shown and you have a possibility to delete the selected templates.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Text Templates</b><br/>
					In this section you can manage text templates which can be used to release the results of the quiz.<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Text Template</b><br/>
						To add / update text template click "Add" button at the page with the of text templates. To update it click the name text template in the template list. While adding / updating you can add the following properties:<br/>
						- Text template name;<br/>
						- Template text;<br/>
						<li><b>Text Template List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of tex templates is shown and you can delete the templates selected.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Quiz Results</b><br/>
					In this section you can look through the results of quizzes passed by users. For convevient search of the quizzes you need you can use a filter which allows to select the results of a particilar quiz or user. Besides the possibility to export the results you have chosen in CSV format.
					<br /><br /><br />
					
					<li><b> Language (Backend / Frontend)</b><br/>
					In this section a possibility to choose the existing language resourses is foreseen. Besides you can add the new ones; a separate interface for backend and frontend is foreseen. You can also export language settings to XML file or import them from XML file.
					<br /><br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Templates</b><br/>
					In this section the management of CSS templates is carried out. They can by used while showing quizzes to users.<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update CSS Template</b><br/>
						To add CSS template click "Add" button at the page with CSS template list, to update click the name CSS template in the template list. While adding / updating you can define the following properties:<br/>
						- Template name;<br/>
						- Template text;<br/>
						<li><b>Question Template List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of CSS template is shown and there is a possibility to delete selected templates.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Quiz List</b><br/>
					In this section you can manage quizzes.<br/><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Quiz</b><br/>
						To create a quiz click "Add" button at the page with the list of quizzes. To update it click quiz name in the list of quizzes. While adding / updating you can define the following properties:<br/>
						- Quiz name;<br/>
						- Category refers to the quiz.(See section 1);<br/>
						- The group of users which have access to the quiz. If "Guest" group is selected all users will have access to the quiz. This option is hierarchical: once you\'ve chosen the "Author" group, than "Author", "Editor" and "Publisher" will have access to the quiz;<br/>
						- Activate or deactivate quiz;<br/>
						- Set the time given to pass a quiz . If meaning "0" or empty is set, the whole time to pass a quiz is not limited but the time for answering questions can be limited;<br/>
						- Set the quantity of scores needed to pass a quiz (in percent);<br/>
						- Set the maximal amount of questions in the quiz, if meaning "0" or empty is set, all questions will be added to quiz question pool;<br/>
						- Set the time given to think of the answer to the question. If meaning "0" or empty is defined the whole time for passing a test is unlimited but it can be redefined on the category of the question level or question level;<br/>
						- Quiz description;<br/>
						- Define a text template to show a user after successful completion of  quiz. If not defined, nothing will be shown to the user after the completion;<br/>
						- Define a text template to show a user if user failed a quiz. If not defined, nothing will be shown to the user after the failure;<br/>
						- Define a text template for printing after the successful completion of a quiz. If not defined, a user will not be able to print the results;<br/>
						- Define a text template for printing  after quiz failure. If not defined, a user will not be able to print the results;<br/>
						- Define a text template for sending to e-mail after successful completion of the quiz. If not defined users will not be able to send the results to their e-mail after successful completion of the quiz;<br/>
						- Define a text template for sending to e-mail after quiz failure. If not defined users will not be able to send the results on their e-mail in the case of failure;<br/>
						- Define CSS Template for showing a quiz to the user;<br/>
						- Allow a user to skip questions and back to them later;<br/>
						- Show questions in occasional order;<br/>
						- Define a period of time which must pass after the completion of the quiz to make it available to a user again. If meaning "0" or empty is defined the quantity is unlimited.(Doesn\'t refer to unregistered users).<br/>
						
						<li><b>Quiz List</b><br/>
						At this page the list of quizzes is shown and there is a possibility to delete selected quizzes or to activate / inactivate them.<br/>
					</ol>
					<br /><br />
					
					<li><b>Questions Management</b><br/>
					<ol style="list-style: lower-alpha;">
						<li><b>Add / Update Question</b><br/>
						To add a question click "Add" button at the page with the list of questions. To update it click the text of the question in the list of questions. While adding / updating you can add the following properties:<br/>
						- Define a question category.(See section 2);<br/>
						- Add a question on the basis of question templates.(See section 3);<br/>
						- Select a type of questions on the basis of which a question will be created. (See section 9.c)<br/>
						- Define quantity of scores for the right answer;<br/>
						- Define the text of question (WYSIWYG editor is used);<br/>
						- Define the parameters for the type of question selected.<br/>

						<li><b>Question List</b><br/>
						To go to the page with the list of quiz questions click view of quiz questions at page Quiz List (See section 9.b). At this page there is a possibility to delete the selected questions or to make a reorder, the order of questions will be taken into consideration if showing questions in order is used in the quiz.<br/>
						
						<li><b>Question Type</b><br/>
						- Single Question: is used for question with two or more answer options, only one of which is true;<br/>
						- Multiple Question: is used for questions with two or more options from which several options must be choosed;<br/>
						- FreeText Question: is used for questions in which the answer must be introduced in the text field. While creating this type of question the user produces correct variants.<br/>
					</ol>
				</ol>
			
		',
    'description' => 'Help text',
  ),
);
?>